events.name: Baylor Bears at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Will Grier threw three touchdown passes and No. 13 West Virginia used a big second quarter to cruise to a 58-14 victory over Baylor on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 WVU uses 31-point second quarter to beat Baylor 58-14

video.headline: Sills grabs and goes for a 65-yard TD

events.name: Appalachian State Mountaineers at Georgia Southern Eagles

headlines.description: Shai Werts rushed for 129 yards, including a 47-yard touchdown run, and Georgia Southern upset No. 25 Appalachian State 34-14 on Thursday night to spoil the Mountaineers' first week in the Top 25.
headlines.shortLinkText: Werts leads Georgia Southern past No. 25 App State 34-14

video.headline: Eagles QB goes 47 yards to the house

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at Ohio Bobcats

headlines.description: Nathan Rourke threw a touchdown pass and ran for two scores and Ohio gained 411 yards on the ground in the Bobcats' 52-14 victory over Ball State on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio runs for 411 yards, overpowers Ball State 52-14

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Western Michigan Broncos

headlines.description: Eli Peters replaced injured starter Mitchell Guadagni and threw three second-half touchdown passes to help Toledo beat Western Michigan 51-24 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toledo's 3rd quarter keys 51-24 win over Western Michigan

video.headline: Toledo's Peters to Gilliam for a 34-yard TD

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Backup quarterback Tobias Oliver ran for 215 yards and three touchdowns and Georgia Tech ran all over Virginia Tech for a 49-28 victory on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oliver, Yellow Jackets run all over Hokies 49-28

video.headline: Georgia Tech extends their lead to 35-21
